5 Planner Mistakes! Let’s get into it! 

We are on a mission to help YOU become the BEST YOU possible! So today we want to highlight five mistakes we see that might be holding you back! 

#1) Not even using one! (This is the biggest and most obvious) While we still use a digital calendar, it is critical to start creating your schedule around WHO you can to become and for that you need an intentional paper planner. 

#2) Only scheduling the ‘urgent’ tasks. If you want to become your best self... your schedule needs to include your fundamental needs and intentional time to build yourself! Is your schedule only used for urgent task?

#3) Overfilled schedule. Are you saying YES to too much, then bashing yourself because you couldn’t get it all done? It’s time to start building a realistic weekly schedule friend! What can you say NO to this week? 

#4) Keeping all work tasks in your paper planner. Whew! I did this for a while and it’s a quick way to get overwhelmed! I highly recommend a task management system for your work tasks (like asana or meistertask to keep your workflow in there!) 

#5) Forgetting to PRAY over your schedule. I highly recommend a weekly planning time each week + make time to PRAY over your scheudule! See what God can do!! 

Follow for more tips! #plannertips #paperplanner #dreamplanner #christianplanner
